<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The condition of Premier Andreas Papandreou
improved today as hospital treatment continued for heart and kidney
problems, doctors said today.
   Papandreou met briefly today with Cyprus President George
Vassiliou and planned talks with the leader of a leftist alliance on
forming a coalition government.
   Papandreou, 70, was admitted to General State Hospital on
Thursday with pneumonia he contracted eight months after undergoing
open heart surgery in London. Hospital officials said he
subsequently experienced heart and kidney complications.
   In a medical bulletin today, a team of doctors said Papandreou
``spent a peaceful night. His treatment continues and his condition
is improving.''
