<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Paris-Jumper     06-26 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Paris-Jumper,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Jumps From Notre Dame; Kills Self, Tourist</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man jumped from the south tower of Notre Dame
cathedral Monday, killing himself and a teen-aged girl standing on
the sidewalk, police said.
   The unidentified man struck Martine Blot, 14, who was part of a
school group from the Charles Peguy College in Paris, police said.
Both died instantly.
   A witness said the girl was standing to the side of her tour
group when she was struck.
   Police have opened an investigation into the incident.
   Police said there have been at least two suicides from the
cathedral tower. The installation of anti-jumping devices at Notre
Dame has been impossible for technical reasons connected with the
lighting of the church, they said.
</TEXT>
