<FIRST>u i PM-Salvador-Shooting     06-26 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Salvador-Shooting,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>National Fire Chief Shot To Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An armed forces colonel who
commanded the national firefighting corps was shot to death while
driving to work today in an attack the military blamed on leftist
rebels.
   Col. Robeto Armando Rivera Escobar, 45, died at the Military
Hospital shortly after the attack this morning, the armed forces
said in a statement.
   Rivera, former head of the National Security Police, was driving
to work alone in the southern part of the capital when three men in
a passing truck opened fire, the military said.
   Police said the attackers were armed with Soviet-made AK-47
assault rifles. They said two sticks of TNT were found on the street
near the scene of the shooting.
   The military blamed Rivera's shooting on urban commandos of the
Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front, the leftist guerrillas
who have been at war with El Salvador's U.S.-backed government for
nine years.
   There was no immediate claim or denial of responsibility.
   Rivera was named head of the firefighting corps, a branch of the
armed forces, three weeks ago by the new rightist administration.
</TEXT>
