<FIRST>r a AM-People-Givens     06-26 0398</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Givens,0412</SECOND>
<HEAD>Robin Givens Says Danger Drew Her To Tyson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RADNOR, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Robin Givens says she still loves
ex-husband Mike Tyson, and the thrill of ``danger'' continues to
draw her to the heavyweight boxing champion.
   ``I loved the danger. ... He was exciting,'' said Givens, who
plays Darlene on the ABC show Head of the Class.
   ``And I think that what people don't realize with a certain type
of woman is that there are times when she wants the man she is with
to be ... a man,'' she said in an interview published in the July 1
issue of TV Guide magazine.
   But she said the qualities that attracted her to Tyson went out
of control after they married. There were times, she said, when he
threaten to kill her, on one occasion even placing a pillow over her
head, and there were times when he hit her.
   ``Michael told me that he was going to kill me and that the world
would be grateful because he's made them think that I'm bad,'' she
said.
   Tyson's attorney, Howard Weitzman, said that when he told Tyson
of the comments, the boxer shrugged and said, ``Come on, man.''
   A new biography of Tyson, ``Fire and Fear: The Inside Story of
Mike Tyson,'' describes him as wife-beater who reportedly said that
he never hit an opponent as hard as he hit Givens on one occasion.
   The two were married Feb. 7, 1988, and Givens filed for divorce
in October. The divorce was finalized last month.
   Givens denied that her mother, Ruth Roper, helped manipulate the
boxer's life during the short-lived marriage.
   ``People always say, `Well, why was your mother around?' I had to
beg this woman (to be around). I couldn't do it by myself,'' she
said.
   Also false, she said, is the rumor that she moved to California
shortly before filing divorce papers to take advantage of that
state's community-property laws.
   ``The funny thing is, not only didn't I get a fortune. I didn't
get anything,'' she said.
   Weitzman said, ``That is just false. She came away from the
marriage with seven-figures-plus.''
   He said she also kept numerous gifts Tyson had given her during
the marriage.
   Givens said, ``Somebody was going to have to bend, and neither of
us could. What people don't understand, what they have forgotten in
all this, is: I love Michael.''
</TEXT>
