<FIRST>r i AM-CounterfeitDollars     06-26 0225</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Counterfeit Dollars,0230</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Report Arresting Gang Distributing Bogus U.S. Money</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested five people
involved in distributing $10 million in bogus U.S. money, capturing
one gang member naked in a bathroom with a pistol, according to a
policeman and a TV network Monday.
   Federal policeman Zildo Heleodoro said $210,000 in counterfeit
bills were recovered in the raid on Saturday in Sao Paulo, 275 miles
southwest of Rio.
   Heleodoro said police felt sure they would recover $9.8 million
more in Rio ``very shortly.''
   TV Globo, Brazil's largest commercial television network,
identified all five arrested as Brazilians. It said police acted on
a tip from U.S. Treasury agents.
   Police were impressed with the quality of the fake bills,
believed to have been made in Leticia, Colombia, on Brazil's
northwestern border, Globo said. It said the four men and one woman
were staying at a hotel near the city center. The network said
police gained admittance to their room by using the knock sequence
employed by callers interested in buying counterfeit bills.
   They arrested four gang members in the room, and then broke down
a locked bathroom door and arrested a naked man armed with a .38
caliber pistol, Globo reported.
   Police believe the gang did business with Brazilians who planned
to travel to the United States, the network reported.
 
</TEXT>
