<HEAD>Millie Is Beautiful</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   First Lady Barbara Bush sprang to the defense
Monday night of her springer spaniel Millie, branded ``ugly'' by a
Washington magazine.
   ``Millie has been slow about writing her book, but this is going
to bring her to action,'' Mrs. Bush told reporters outside the White
House after returning with President Bush from a parade at the
Marine Barracks.
   What got the firt lady's pique was an item in Washingtonian
magazine, in its annual best-and-worst rankings of capital doings,
that accorded Millie the dubious honor of ``best'' ugly dog.
   The magazine said the White House canine has not bitten the
president yet, ``but let's face it: This is a very homely springer
spaniel.''
   If Millie harbors literary ambitions, she will be the second
straight Bush dog to achieve authordom.
   Mrs. Bush was the ghostwriter of her previous pet's
autobiography, ``C. Fred's Story,'' to raise funds for charity.
